   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR THE NEW TESTAMENT PRIESTLY SERVICE 1 Scripture Reading: Rev 1:5-6; Rom 15:16; 1 Pet 2:5, 9; Eph 3:2; 1 Cor 9:16-17; Eph 3:8; John 15:16; Psa 119:147-148; Rom 8:37; Eph 5:18b; 2 Tim 4:2a; John 21:15; 1 Thes 2:7; Eph 4:11-12; Heb 10:24-25; 1 Thes 2:11 OUTLINE All the New Testament believers being priests to serve God Rev 1:5-6.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The priests of the gospel of God Rom 15:16: Being built up into God's holy priesthood the whole church becoming the New Testament priesthood of the gospel 1 Pet 2:5a.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Telling out the virtues such as love, grace, and forgiveness of the One who has saved us out of darkness into His marvelous light 1 Pet 2:9.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Carrying out the stewardship of the grace of God in God's economy Eph 3:2; 1 Cor 9:16-17.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Ministering to others the unsearchable riches of Christ as the grace of God Eph 3:8.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Offering up spiritual sacrifices acceptable to God, that is, offering up the saved sinners as members of Christ to constitute the Body of Christ 1 Pet 2:5; Rom 15:16b.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Being chosen and appointed by God to bear remaining fruit John 15:16.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The living of the priests of the gospel of God: Being revived every morning Psa 119:147-148.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Overcoming every day Rom 8:37.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Being filled with the Spirit every moment Eph 5:18b.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Speaking Christ everywhere 2 Tim 4:2a.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Feeding the lambs in the Lord's flock John 21:15: Through the home meetings in the new believers' homes.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>As a nursing mother would cherish her own babes 1 Thes 2:7.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Perfecting the saints Eph 4:11-12: Through the group meetings: Not a religious service.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Not a Bible-study meeting.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>But the Christians' own assembling for considering one another, inciting one another to love and good works, and exhorting one another Heb 10:24-25.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Bringing the new believers who are under our nourishing to attend the group meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Besides the mutual fellowship, intercession, care, shepherding, and testifying, the main thing in the group meetings being to teach one another that all may be perfected.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Entreating and consoling the believers and testifying to them as a father to his own children 1 Thes 2:11.</S>
   </TEXT>
